The paper discusses problem-driven visualization projects and design studies, which are typically associated with the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) and Visualization (cs.VIS) sub-categories. The paper also emphasizes the importance of transdisciplinary collaboration, which could fall under the Cybersecurity (cs.CYBER) or Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the challenges and potential pitfalls of the proposed methodological paradigm, which could be relevant to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
